# Tools

Some simple tools for my own productivity.

---

## pass - Password Store Replacement

Windows-compatible `pass` (password-store) replacement in Go. Manages GPG-encrypted password files in `~/.password-store/` with git integration.

### Features

- GPG-encrypted password storage
- Git integration for version control
- **New: Git status and operations** (`pass git`, `pass git push`, `pass git update`)
- Interactive fuzzy search with TUI (Bubble Tea)
- Git status displayed in TUI
- Cross-platform (Windows, Linux, macOS)
- Copy to clipboard support
- Edit existing passwords with your favorite editor

### Build
```bash
cd pass && ./build.sh          # native build → ../shell/pass[.exe]
cd pass && ./build.sh build    # same
cd pass && ./build.sh build-all # cross-compile linux amd64/arm64 + windows arm64
```

### Install
```bash
# Windows: copy pass.exe to PATH
copy shell\pass.exe C:\Windows\System32\

# Linux/macOS:
sudo cp shell/pass /usr/local/bin/
```

### Test
```bash
# Run tests
cd pass
go test ./...

# Manual test
./pass.exe ls
./pass.exe find gmail
./pass.exe insert test/password
```

### Usage
```bash
# Password management
pass ls                    # List passwords (files only)
pass find gmail            # Search
pass email/gmail.com/user  # Show password
pass -c email/...          # Copy to clipboard
pass insert email/...      # Add new password (fails if exists)
pass edit email/...        # Edit existing password in $EDITOR
pass edit                 # Interactive fuzzy search to edit
pass                       # Interactive fuzzy search TUI
pass -c                   # Interactive fuzzy search with clipboard copy
pass rm                   # Interactive fuzzy search to remove

# Git integration (new!)
pass git                  # Show git status of password store
pass git -v               # Show detailed git status
pass git push             # Push changes to remote
pass git update           # Pull changes from remote
pass git init             # Initialize git repository
pass git status           # Alias for 'pass git'
```

### TUI

When running `pass`, `pass -c`, `pass rm`, or `pass edit` without arguments, an interactive TUI is displayed:
- Use up/down arrows to navigate the list
- Use left/right arrows to move cursor in search input
- Use Tab to cycle through results
- Type to filter passwords using fuzzy matching (subsequence matching)
- Press Enter to select (show, copy, remove, or edit based on command)
- Press Esc, Ctrl+C, Ctrl+D, or Ctrl+Q to exit

**Git operations in TUI:**
- Git status is displayed in the header (e.g., `Git: main ⬆2⬇1 *`)
- `Ctrl+P` - Push changes to remote
- `Ctrl+U` - Pull changes from remote
- `Ctrl+R` - Refresh git status

**Status symbols:**
- `*` = uncommitted changes
- `!` = merge conflicts
- `⬆N` = N commits ahead of remote
- `⬇N` = N commits behind remote
- `=` = up to date

### Configuration

- `PASSWORD_STORE_DIR`: Custom password store location (default: `~/.password-store`)
- `EDITOR`: Editor to use for editing passwords (default: `notepad` on Windows, `vi` on Unix)
- Requires GPG to be installed and configured

### Prerequisites
- Go 1.20+
- GnuPG (GPG4Win on Windows)
- Git (optional, for version control)

---

## gitprompt - Git Prompt Utility

Git prompt utility for shell integration.

### Build
```bash
cd gitprompt && ./build.sh          # native build → ../shell/gitprompt[.exe]
cd gitprompt && ./build.sh build    # same
cd gitprompt && ./build.sh build-all # cross-compile linux amd64/arm64 + windows arm64
```

### Install
```bash
# Windows: copy gitprompt.exe to PATH
copy shell\gitprompt.exe C:\Windows\System32\

# Linux/macOS:
sudo cp shell/gitprompt /usr/local/bin/
```

### Prerequisites
- Go 1.25+ (go-git v5.19 dependency)

---

## Building All Tools

Use the wrapper script to build both tools at once:
```bash
./shell/make.sh          # build both gitprompt and pass
./shell/make.sh build    # same
./shell/make.sh build-all # cross-compile both
./shell/make.sh clean    # clean both builds
```
